				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Bard xp bot  &gt;&lt;<a name="41910"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 24 04 6:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I was in the Plane of Nightmare yesterday, and come to think of it, this isn't the first time I've seen this guy.  It didn't occur to me before that this was a bot, but now I'm sure of it.
<br />

<br />

<br />
This level 65 bard has a spot near the stalkers camp, but not at it, where he runs continuously in a near perfect circle doing nothing but aggroing mobs (trees, birds, and spiders) for a time, then targets one of them and chants it down.  Then rinses and repeats.
<br />

<br />
I have watched the circles carefully and they are very accurate.  I sent him a couple of tells and no response.  He even runs in perfect circles when there are no mobs behind him.
<br />

<br />
He also has a cleric that sits up on the hill nearby, probably soaking up xp and buffing Hand of Virtue every hour or two.  Or maybe just soaking xp... I don't know.
<br />

<br />
I'm on The Nameless, and this character's name is Plugisse, and his cleric's name is Frogisse. They are both members of a Taiwanese guild named Kylin Eyes.
<br />

<br />
I /petition'd this behavior to the GM, but I doubt they will do anything about it.
<br />

<br />
This makes me mad &gt;&lt;
<br />

<br />
If I was a rooting class I'd be very tempted to root some mobs in this guy's circle.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
