				<td colspan="2"><span>PoN on most servers, has a bot/macro bard running around in it every few months.  They're usually simple keyboard macros that run them in perfect circles and chant down the nearest mob.  The last two that I saw on Drinal were both banned but there's a new one who just popped up.  
<br />

<br />
The first time I saw this the guy ran in circles out between the cliff and the GY and he only killed ravens, no matter what was chasing him he picked out the ravens, obviuosly because his macro contained &quot;/target a blood raven&quot;.  The newest one though simply targets whatever is closest to him as if he wer ehitting F8.
<br />

<br />
You have to be very careful about this though, the circles I run are pretty d*mn near perfect too and if I'm chant kiting I do not have time to stop and respond to /tells until the mobs chasing me are dead.  I don't really chant anymore unless it's a weak mob that I dont' feal like swarming, when I solo I invariably swarm.  If there's enough room to chant kite there's enough room to swarm kite and if I'm in a dungeon or something I melee the mobs down.
<br />

<br />
/report the guy, let the GM's sort it out, if you go purposefully killing an active player who was just too busy to respond you'll end up being the one who gets banned.</span></td>
