				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Define large circles, then define a small circle and a medium one in game.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Small circle: done with arrows+enter, or a really tightly timed running plus hitting arrows fast.
<br />

<br />
Medium circle: ... bah.. no reason for this one really
<br />

<br />
Large circle: as in way too large to AE kite, but well within range of a chant.   No way would AE hit these mobs at this distance, and he was not AEing them.
<br />

<br />
You know how I verified he wasn't?  I looked at the health of each mob using target cycling.  Only one of the mobs had a health percentage less than 100%.  And sometimes, ALL of them were at 100% for minutes at a time, because of some innefficiency in the coding of the bot, I'm guessing.  It may do a &quot;target nearest&quot; when there are no mobs trailing him and then start the 3 minute chant cycle on no target... and during that 3 minutes of chanting at nothing, he aggros up a few mobs.
<br />

<br />
Come on ... I'm a level 65 bard that's been playing for almost 3 years and have spent quite a lot of time kiting, grouping, raiding, etc...  give me a little credit for being able to tell what's going on here.
<br />

